{"id": "lunchcultuur-in-de-lage-landen-kansen-voor-bourgondische-lunchrevolutie__a2-late-chunking__0004", "text": "Burgundian Lunch Index 2025 shows a gap of 35 percent in the average lunch voucher: Belgian guests pay an average of 38.20 euros for lunch, while Dutch guests pay 28.05 euros. This gap reflects more than just economic differences; she shows how deeply lunch habits are culturally anchored. Where the Dutch use midday for speed and efficiency, Belgians use the same time for contact, comfort and culinary experience.", "metadata": {"chunk_id": "lunchcultuur-in-de-lage-landen-kansen-voor-bourgondische-lunchrevolutie__a2-late-chunking__0004", "source_slug": "lunchcultuur-in-de-lage-landen-kansen-voor-bourgondische-lunchrevolutie", "source_title": "Lunch culture in the Low Countries: opportunities for a Burgundian lunch revolution", "source_url": "https://www.abnamro.nl/nl/zakelijk/insights/sectoren-en-trends/leisure/lunchcultuur-in-de-lage-landen-kansen-voor-bourgondische-lunchrevolutie.html", "source_date": "2025-06-13", "doc_type": "article", "channel": "website", "content_type": "insight_article", "sector": "leisure", "topic": "sectoren en trends", "language_original": "nl", "language_embedded": "en", "translation_method": "deep-translator", "translated_with": "deep-translator", "chunker": "a2-late-chunking", "chunk_index": 4, "n_chunks_total": 20, "status": "approved", "date_ingested": "2026-04-30", "requires_late_chunking": true, "source_doc_offset": 4}}
